## Closing Note

This walkthrough intentionally stays at the "standard methodology" level — Nmap for recon, OpenVAS/Nessus for automated vulnerability identification, and CVE/CVSS for prioritization — which mirrors how a real internal VA is structured. The real-world references above are included for context on *why* each finding matters, not as exploitation instructions; exploitation/post-exploitation (e.g., via Metasploit modules) is a separate phase with its own authorization requirements and is outside the scope of this assessment guide.
